{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Observed in this behavior: verifies cross-module handoff from three source collectors into the summary-input builder. Hypothetical elsewhere: real network/API outages, model quality. MOCK-MISS: yes, failure is at module boundaries (missing one source in composed payload), not a single-function algorithm. REAL-INFRA: no explicit need for real OS/network/subprocess; in-process fakes for the three sources can reproduce omission bugs. LLM-DEP: no, this checks input completeness, not generated quality. MULTI-STEP: no agentic chain. Rejection gate: System/Agentic rejected because behavior text only requires \"content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources,\" which is satisfiable with wired modules and stubbed sources.","test_description":"Wire the real orchestration path with three stub source adapters returning distinct sentinel fields; execute data collection + composition; assert the exact payload sent to the summary step contains all three source sections and key fields, and fails if any section is dropped/overwritten.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Observed in this behavior: partial-failure handling across source adapter, report assembler, and error-to-note mapping. Hypothetical elsewhere: real timeout semantics, SMTP outages. MOCK-MISS: yes, boundary behavior matters (exception/failed fetch propagated into section note) and is best caught with modules wired together. REAL-INFRA: no explicit requirement for real network; a stubbed failing adapter reproduces unavailable-source conditions for this behavior. LLM-DEP: no, requirement is fallback note presence and non-abort. MULTI-STEP: no. Rejection gate: System rejected because behavior text says only \"when one data source is unavailable\" and does not require validating real transport/network behavior.","test_description":"Run report generation with two source adapters returning data and one adapter raising an availability error; assert process exits successfully, output report includes normal sections for available sources, and unavailable section contains the exact `data unavailable` marker instead of terminating.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Observed in this behavior: semantic fidelity of narrative output to input key values. Hypothetical elsewhere: email transport, scheduler reliability. MOCK-MISS: yes; deterministic mocks of summary generation would likely always pass and hide hallucination/misstatement failures. REAL-INFRA: not primarily OS/network/subprocess unless needed to call the model API; core boundary is model output quality. LLM-DEP: yes, correctness depends on actual summary-generation output quality and potential non-determinism. MULTI-STEP: no explicit multiple agentic stages, just one summary step. Rejection gate: Integration rejected because behavior text requires the summary to \"accurately represent\" key values, which cannot be validated against real failure modes using fixed stub responses alone.","test_description":"Use representative input datasets with known key values; invoke the real summary generator repeatedly; score each output for factual consistency against required key facts (presence and correctness thresholds), and fail on omissions, incorrect numeric statements, or contradictory claims beyond tolerance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.28,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.62,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Observed in this behavior: end-to-end execution including real delivery outcome in a recipient inbox. Hypothetical elsewhere: model semantic quality beyond basic completion. MOCK-MISS: yes; mocked mail send can pass while real SMTP/API auth, serialization, or delivery path fails. REAL-INFRA: yes, requires real external email service/inbox behavior. LLM-DEP: not required for this specific assertion; message content can be deterministic fixture-driven. MULTI-STEP: no multi-agentic chain requirement. Rejection gate: Agentic/Workflow rejected because behavior text focuses on delivery success to inbox, not model-quality or multi-agent reasoning.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled script in a test environment using real endpoints (or production-like test accounts) through actual email transport; verify the configured recipient inbox receives one report email with expected subject/body structure and source-derived sections.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Observed in this behavior: failure handling path across email sender, local persistence, and subsequent-run retry logic. Hypothetical elsewhere: real cron timing drift, real network packet behavior. MOCK-MISS: yes for module interaction (send failure -> persist -> reload -> resend), but can be reproduced with in-process failing sender and real local filesystem. REAL-INFRA: no mandatory real network/subprocess; local filesystem is allowed at Integration level. LLM-DEP: no, retry logic independent of model quality. MULTI-STEP: no agentic chain. Rejection gate: System rejected because behavior text requires unreachable service handling plus local save/retry, which can be validated by simulating sender unreachability and invoking two runs with persisted state.","test_description":"First run: use a sender adapter that returns unreachable error; assert report is written to retry file/queue and process does not lose payload. Second run: use reachable sender; assert previously saved report is sent and retry artifact is cleared/marked delivered.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.64,"System":0.24,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
